sri-project-1 | 3D Complex Mapping in Urban Terrain | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/3d-complex-mapping-urban-terrain | description:SRI is developing technology that will enable warfighters to easily maneuver a robot, precisely map an environment, and have 3D situational awareness.
sri-project-2 | Adaptable Sensor System for Real-Time Data on the Front Line | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/adaptable-sensor-system | description:DARPA taps SRI to deliver usable video and analytics to U.S. Armed Forces when and where they need it.
sri-project-3 | AURORA: Content-Guided Search of Diverse Videos | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/aurora | description:SRI is developing a novel search technology to quickly find events of interest in very large video collections.
sri-project-4 | Automated Performance Evaluation and Lessons Learned | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/apell | description:SRI’s mixed reality training system provides comprehensive mission rehearsal tools to improve warfighter training.
sri-project-5 | Hierarchical Urban and Natural Terrain Exploitation and Reasoning | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/hunter | description:SRI is developing a system for the semi-automated geolocalization of metadata-free images and videos to find a location of interest.
sri-project-6 | Pedestrian Detection from Moving Unmanned Ground Vehicles | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/pedestrian-detection-moving-unmanned-ground-vehicles | description:SRI’s vision-based systems enable safe operations of moving unmanned ground vehicles around stationary and moving people in urban or cluttered environments.
sri-project-7 | Tracking Humans in Crowds | http://www.sri.com/work/projects/tracking-humans-crowds | description:SRI is developing a prototype system to automatically detect and track multiple individuals in a crowd.
